# Goal Description
Build a modern, responsive frontend for the Smart Triage System using Next.js (App Router), Tailwind CSS, and Shadcn UI.
The application will consist of a public ticket submission page for customers, and a protected agent dashboard for managing tickets with optimistic UI updates.

## Proposed Changes

### Setup and Scaffolding
- Initialize Next.js 14+ application with App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and ESLint in the `frontend` directory.
- Setup Shadcn UI components (button, input, form, select, table, badge, toast, tabs/kanban).

### API Integration and State
- Create `lib/api.ts` representing the client for the OpenAPI spec.
- Implemented fetching logic directly using fetch API or an SWR/React Query approach for caching and optimistic updates.
- Setup an Auth Context (`components/providers/auth-provider.tsx`) or similar state management to hold the `access_token` and `user_id`, protected via strictly checked routes or middleware.

### Frontend Routing and Pages
#### Public Routes
- **`/`**: Landing/Customer Submission Page
  - Uses a Shadcn form schema (Zod) matching `CreateTicketRequest` (`title`, `description`).
  - Calls `POST /api/v1/customer/ticket`.
  - Shows success toast on submission.
- **`/login`**: Agent Login Page
  - Calls `POST /api/v1/auth/login`.
  - Redirects to `/dashboard` on success.
- **`/register`**: Agent Registration
  - Calls `POST /api/v1/auth/register`.
- **`/verify`**: OTP Verification
  - Calls `POST /api/v1/auth/send-verification-otp` and `POST /api/v1/auth/verify-otp`.

#### Protected Routes (Agent)
- **`/dashboard`**: Kanban / Data Table of Tickets
  - Calls `GET /api/v1/ticket/ticket` with pagination/filtering.
  - UI for tickets, showing `title`, `description`, `status`, `priority`, `category`.
  - Includes a dropdown/status select per ticket. Changes to status trigger an optimistic ui update for `PATCH /api/v1/ticket/ticket/{ticket_id}` using `TicketStatusRequest`.

### Styling & Interactivity
- Create a modern, dark-mode supported dashboard with glassmorphism or sleek minimalist aesthetics.
- Animations on ticket open/close, drag-and-drop or simple instant status toggle with toast feedback.

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
- Verify that a customer can submit a ticket from the landing page.
- Verify that an agent can register, login, and potentially verify their email (if necessary for login).
- Verify the agent dashboard loads tickets.
- Verify updating a ticket status works and reflects instantly in the UI (optimistic update).
